aVTrump plans to visit Texas early next week in response to Hurricane Harvey\u000a\u000aPresident Donald Trump plans to visit Texas early next week as it copes with the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey, White House press secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders said on Friday.\u000a\u000aSpeaking at the White House briefing, Sanders said details of the president's visit will be released as soon as they are finalized.\u000a\u000aStory Continued Below\u000a\u000aTrump will spend the weekend in Camp David, though White House officials said the president will be in full communication with the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to stay updated on the unfolding events.\u000a\u000a\u201cThis is right up President Trump\u2019s alley,\u201d White House homeland security adviser Tom Bossert said of Trump's preparations for a response to the hurricane. \u201cNot only has he showed leadership but he is focused on the Americans that voted him into office. He\u2019s focused on the Americans that didn\u2019t vote him into office. He\u2019s focused on effecting positive change in this country.\u201d\u000a\u000aTrump is also scheduled to hold an event in Missouri next week to tout a tax overhaul \u2014 one of his top legislative priorities.\u000a\u000aAuthors:
