aVU.S. President Donald Trump | Pool photo by Chris Kleponis/Getty Images Most Americans say Trump\u2019s behavior \u2018not what I expect from a president\u2019: poll Survey comes amid a rocky month for the president.\u000a\u000aPresident Donald Trump promised to bring a fresh, outsider approach to the Oval Office, but about 7 in 10 voters nonetheless say the commander in chief\u2019s behavior \u201cis not what I expect from a president,\u201d according to a poll released Thursday.\u000a\u000aThe George Washington University poll found that 71 percent of voters had that view of Trump\u2019s comportment in office, while 27 percent disagreed that his behavior was not what they expected.\u000a\u000aSixty-eight percent of registered voters said Trump\u2019s actions and rhetoric \u201ccould get us accidentally involved in an international conflict,\u201d while 29 percent disagreed with that statement, the poll found.\u000a\u000aThe poll comes amid a rocky August for the president, who has faced criticism for his response after a white supremacist rally in Charlottesville, Virginia, left one counterprotester dead. The poll also found that 42 percent of voters approve of the job Trump has done so far in office, while 55 percent disapprove. Fifty-six percent of registered voters said Trump has not been an effective president, while 39 percent said he had been.\u000a\u000aThe portion of voters with a favorable view of Trump \u2014 41 percent, compared to 56 percent with an unfavorable view \u2014 was higher in the poll than for both House Speaker Paul Ryan and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, with 36 percent and 19 percent respectively viewing them favorably.\u000a\u000aBoth Republican congressional leaders have drawn ire from the president in recent days over the GOP\u2019s stalled legislative agenda \u2014 most notably a failure to follow through on a seven-year effort to repeal and replace the Affordable Care Act.\u000a\u000aThe poll surveyed 1,009 registered voters nationwide from August 13-17, and it had a margin of error of plus or minus 3.1 percentage points.
